<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-wNFpRhCJyDhKwcqNY4qXHA" name="define_ent_tool_configs,_OTC-wEmIEd-H4JlF2fadEg" guid="-wNFpRhCJyDhKwcqNY4qXHA" changeDate="2010-08-25T13:01:55.796-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Good processes should be supported by good tools that help make the process run smoothly.&amp;nbsp; Enterprise tool&#xD;
    configurations may be hosted for use by projects, or simply be documented for someone on the project to use when&#xD;
    configuring the tool.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_sE5MkLCDEd-dpZ5d180AQw" name="Determine the enterprise needs in term of tool support" guid="_sE5MkLCDEd-dpZ5d180AQw">
    <sectionDescription>Identify the kind of tools required and how they can help to achieve enterprise goals.&amp;nbsp; This may be part of a larger&#xD;
enterprise effort.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_uqcSgLCDEd-dpZ5d180AQw" name="Determine the scope and usage policy of the tools" guid="_uqcSgLCDEd-dpZ5d180AQw">
    <sectionDescription>Identify who needs to use which tools and how these tools will be made available to their users.&amp;nbsp; For example, will&#xD;
the tool be deployed for projects to use, or do projects need to install something themselves.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_8f3xQLCDEd-dpZ5d180AQw" name="Setup and configure enterprise tools" guid="_8f3xQLCDEd-dpZ5d180AQw">
    <sectionDescription>For tools that are provided by the enterprise, they need to be installed and configured.&amp;nbsp; For tools which are&#xD;
installed by someone else, you need to setup and configure the tool in order to confirm that the configuration works as&#xD;
expected.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_8W2GMLCFEd-dpZ5d180AQw" name="Analyze and revise enterprise tool scope and policy" guid="_8W2GMLCFEd-dpZ5d180AQw">
    <sectionDescription>Analyze the effectiveness of tools installed and determine if changes are necessary to maximize the benefit of these tools.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>The purpose of this task is to define configurations of tools that have been proven to work effectively and fit with the&#xD;
processes defined for the organization.&amp;nbsp;</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
